modules.description: This library provides command-line argument parsing capabilities, including initializing and finalizing argument processing, extracting typed values (integers, strings, booleans, etc.) by key, and handling boolean flags with optional default values. It operates on raw arguments transformed into a string list, supporting both mandatory parameters and optional values that fallback to defaults when unspecified. Common use cases include processing configuration flags (e.g., enabling features or setting thresholds) where missing options should assume predefined values.

This module processes command-line arguments, allowing extraction of typed values by key, handling boolean flags with defaults, and managing required and optional parameters. It works with string lists representing raw arguments, supporting integers, strings, booleans, and custom default values. Concrete use cases include configuring application settings from the command line, such as setting log levels, enabling debug modes, or specifying input files.
